  "prompt": "How do I search if any of my friends and relatives are here on Quora?",
  "response": "Quora doesn\u2019t have a direct feature to search for friends or relatives specifically. However, you can try the following methods to see if people you know are on Quora:\n\n1. **Search by Name**: Use the search bar at the top of the Quora page to type in the names of friends or relatives. Sometimes, their profiles will appear if they\u2019ve used their real names.\n\n2. **Connect via Facebook**: If you\u2019ve linked your Facebook account to Quora, you can go to **Settings > Privacy > Friends & Contacts** and allow Quora to suggest people you might know based on your Facebook connections.\n\n3. **Check Your Email Contacts**: You can also sync your email contacts with Quora by going to **Settings > Privacy > Friends & Contacts** and importing your contacts. Quora will then suggest people you might know.\n\n4. **Look for Mutual Connections**: If you find one person you know, check their followers or the people they\u2019re following. You might find other friends or relatives there.\n\n5. **Search for Specific Topics**: If your friends or relatives are active on Quora, they might have answered questions or followed topics related to their interests. Searching for those topics might lead you to their profiles.\n\nRemember, people might not always use their real names or public profiles on Quora, so it\u2019s possible that some friends or relatives might not be easily findable.",
